originalText.text: These people are horrible and the wait is long with or with an appointment. It's very hot inside of there, tend to always be crowded too. The drop off service is no better. The site manager has a bad body odor and lack the ability to read the items in from of her (documents provided). And they don't call you the next day as promised. Went there 3 times in a week span to file taxes for 2016 and 2017, yet still only filed 2016 taxes. 2 thumbs down for this tax site.

originalText.text: On 3/26/22 I came in for 2:00pm appointment  at 71 Saint Nicholas Ave location and still had to wait. In addition to that, the young African man that was my tax preparer was EXTREMELY rude! As soon as I got to his desk he kept huffing and puffing and saying how tired he was, caught me at the wrong time, etc. very bad attitude. Then once he got to my W2’s he said oh you have five W2’s and greatly rolled his eyes about it with no shame. I was so uncomfortable and disgusted by his unprofessional behavior I didn’t know what to do but stay glued to my phone! Thankfully the woman that reviewed my taxes was actually PROFESSIONAL! Everyone was except for that one guy! I traveled too far to get such a rude service! I’ve always used food bank for tax preparations and I’ve never encountered such bad attitude from one of the staff before until today!
